\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 330, \"end\": 336, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"score\": 0.9999999766064323, \"rank\": 2.3004973949475396e-08, \"text\": \"Taiwan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\"}, {\"begin\": 423, \"end\": 430, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9133396482989139, \"rank\": 0.09090985641754352, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Wang Chi-Lin and Lee Yang of Taiwan, the reigning champions from the 2021 Tokyo Olympics, won a three-game thriller against China's Liang Weikeng and Wang Chang.\", \"from\": 547, \"to\": 708, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 547, \"end\": 559, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wang_Chi-lin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Wang Chi-Lin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wang_Chi-lin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wang_Chi-lin\"}, {\"begin\": 564, \"end\": 572, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lee_Yang\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lee Yang\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lee_Yang\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lee_Yang\"}, {\"begin\": 576, \"end\": 582, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"score\": 0.9999999766064323, \"rank\": 2.3004973949475396e-08, \"text\": \"Taiwan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\"}, {\"begin\": 671, \"end\": 676, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"score\": 0.9999999687770473, \"rank\": 2.7005057031953922e-08, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\"}, {\"begin\": 679, \"end\": 692, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Liang_Weikeng\", \"score\": 0.9999956228389538, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Liang Weikeng\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Liang_Weikeng\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Liang_Weikeng\"}, {\"begin\": 697, \"end\": 707, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wang_Jipeng\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8362780238789854e-16, \"text\": \"Wang Chang\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wang_Jipeng\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wang_Jipeng\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In cities across Taiwan, from Wang's home in the capital Taipei to southern Kaohsiung, and Lee's hometown on the island of Kinmen just off the coast of China, public screens were set up that lured thousands of fans.\", \"from\": 710, \"to\": 925, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 727, \"end\": 733, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"score\": 0.9999999766064323, \"rank\": 2.3004973949475396e-08, \"text\": \"Taiwan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\"}, {\"begin\": 767, \"end\": 773, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"score\": 0.9988178882179244, \"rank\": 0.0007959913783830066, \"text\": \"Taipei\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\"}, {\"begin\": 786, \"end\": 795, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaohsiung\", \"score\": 0.9999993342450977, \"rank\": 6.657552486114637e-07, \"text\": \"Kaohsiung\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaohsiung\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaohsiung\"}, {\"begin\": 801, \"end\": 804, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\", \"score\": 0.8076974934210979, \"rank\": 0.23808728895515716, \"text\": \"Lee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\"}, {\"begin\": 862, \"end\": 867, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"score\": 0.9999999687770473, \"rank\": 2.7005057031953922e-08, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Many were eager to see the island win its first gold medal of the Paris Games against the sporting goliath of China that has already won 19 golds.\", \"from\": 927, \"to\": 1073, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1037, \"end\": 1042, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"score\": 0.9999999687770473, \"rank\": 2.7005057031953922e-08, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Over 1,000 spectators packed into the hall of Taipei's main train station, cheering and applauding each point won by the home duo, and falling silent at every point lost.\", \"from\": 1075, \"to\": 1245, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1121, \"end\": 1127, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"score\": 0.9988178882179244, \"rank\": 0.0007959913783830066, \"text\": \"Taipei\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some waved Taiwan flags and chanted \\\"Support Taiwan!\\\"\", \"from\": 1246, \"to\": 1299, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1257, \"end\": 1263, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"score\": 0.9999999766064323, \"rank\": 2.3004973949475396e-08, \"text\": \"Taiwan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As with previous Olympics, Taiwan's international status has been thrust into the spotlight given its longstanding sovereignty disputes with China.\", \"from\": 1301, \"to\": 1448, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1328, \"end\": 1334, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"score\": 0.9999999766064323, \"rank\": 2.3004973949475396e-08, \"text\": \"Taiwan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\"}, {\"begin\": 1442, \"end\": 1447, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"score\": 0.9999999687770473, \"rank\": 2.7005057031953922e-08, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The island competes as 'Chinese Taipei' rather than as Taiwan, to avoid objections from China, which claims the island as its own territory.\", \"from\": 1450, \"to\": 1590, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1482, \"end\": 1488, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"score\": 0.9988178882179244, \"rank\": 0.0007959913783830066, \"text\": \"Taipei\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\"}, {\"begin\": 1505, \"end\": 1511, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"score\": 0.9999999766064323, \"rank\": 2.3004973949475396e-08, \"text\": \"Taiwan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\"}, {\"begin\": 1538, \"end\": 1543, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"score\": 0.9999999687770473, \"rank\": 2.7005057031953922e-08, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We want to beat China because of the political situation,\\\" said Irene Lai, a 27-year-old office worker who was watching with her boyfriend near the back of the packed Taipei station.\", \"from\": 1592, \"to\": 1775, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1609, \"end\": 1614, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"score\": 0.9999999687770473, \"rank\": 2.7005057031953922e-08, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\"}, {\"begin\": 1657, \"end\": 1662, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irene_of_Athens\", \"score\": 0.9972922923323614, \"rank\": 0.0026729515479168115, \"text\": \"Irene\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irene_of_Athens\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irene_of_Athens\"}, {\"begin\": 1663, \"end\": 1666, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lai_people\", \"score\": 0.9837337620682426, \"rank\": 0.01653480873082198, \"text\": \"Lai\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lai_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lai_people\"}, {\"begin\": 1760, \"end\": 1766, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"score\": 0.9988178882179244, \"rank\": 0.0007959913783830066, \"text\": \"Taipei\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Prior to the final, some Taiwanese supporters arriving at the Paris venue were forced to rub off face paintings of the Taiwan flag, while others had banners confiscated as security staff enforced Olympic rules on political messaging.\", \"from\": 1777, \"to\": 2010, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1802, \"end\": 1811, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"score\": 0.9007778787331925, \"rank\": 0.09676274649594854, \"text\": \"Ta